00:54:41.979 --> 00:54:47.340
Nirama, I wanted to ask you a question that we like to ask everybody, which is, have you

00:54:47.340 --> 00:54:52.300
gotten any really good career advice or given any really good career advice that you could

00:54:52.300 --> 00:54:52.860
share with us?

00:54:53.899 --> 00:54:56.379
Okay, I'm going to give you heartfelt career advice.

00:54:56.379 --> 00:54:56.780
Okay.

00:54:56.780 --> 00:54:58.780
If you want to get promoted, manage up.

00:54:59.580 --> 00:55:00.080
Okay.

00:55:00.699 --> 00:55:06.139
If, on the other hand, you actually want to solve important problems, manage down.

00:55:07.260 --> 00:55:11.659
And the reason I say that is that your ability to solve problems is your ability to go get

00:55:11.659 --> 00:55:12.699
data from your peers.

00:55:12.699 --> 00:55:14.939
So managing down assumes your peer level.

00:55:15.500 --> 00:55:19.419
So take care of the people at your level, take care of the people below you, and they

00:55:19.419 --> 00:55:20.620
will take care of you back.

00:55:22.219 --> 00:55:27.580
It might not get you promoted, but it just makes for a better work environment.

00:55:29.100 --> 00:55:31.500
And I think more impact long term.

00:55:33.260 --> 00:55:38.459
So, and if you want to learn how to manage up, I can find you people to talk to.

00:55:39.020 --> 00:55:40.379
Just don't listen to me.

00:55:41.419 --> 00:55:42.219
Don't be blunt.

00:55:42.219 --> 00:55:44.139
Don't make anyone uncomfortable.

00:55:44.139 --> 00:55:44.379
Right?

00:55:44.379 --> 00:55:48.459
But in order to innovate, you need to be able to have trust and make people uncomfortable

00:55:48.459 --> 00:55:49.739
and make people think differently.

00:55:49.739 --> 00:55:52.139
And if they won't think differently, then they're not going to innovate.

00:55:55.979 --> 00:55:56.620
